definition.value: A hydroxyisoflavanone that is isoflavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 2' and a methoxy group at position 4'.
A secondary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of morpholine resulting from the protonation of the NH group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxyphenylpyruvic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a 3-hydroxyphenyl group.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2,2-dihydroxy-3-methylbutanoic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A CMP-sugar in which the sugar component consists of any N-acyl-beta-neuraminic acid.
A 2-hydroxy fatty acid that is  isovaleric acid  bearing two hydroxy substituents at position 2.

The conjugate base of N-all-trans-retinylidenephosphatidylethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.

A bromoindole that is 2,3,5-tribromo-1H-indole which is substituted by a 5,7-dibromo-3-cyano-1H-indol-2-yl group at position 1. It is a biindole alkaloid isolated from the cyanobacterium Aetokthonos hydrillicola and causes vacuolar myelinopathy in bald eagles.
The conjugate base of N-11-cis-retinylidenephosphatidylethanolamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An alkaloid containing a biindole skeleton.
